
                       Simple De-Archiving Information.
                       --------------------------------

  1) This software is ~(C)1990 Stephen L Childress.~ and its use is
     subject to HIS terms and conditions.
  2) Ensure that you have a copy of the De-Archiving software ~LHA~
     somewhere in the computers' PATH.
  3) It can be downloaded from AMINET or found on many CDROMs.
  4) Double click on the ~De-Archive~ icon and the hidden
     ~©Stephen_L_Childress.lha~ file will expand into the ~AmigaScope~
     drawer.
  5) There are four files in the ~©Stephen_L_Childress.lha~ archive:-
     A) ~AmigaScope.info~, an icon designed by myself.
     B) ~AmigaScope.lha~, the archive as is from AMINET.
     C) ~AmigaScope.readme, The ~readme~ file as is from AMINET.
     D) ~AmigaScope.readme.info~, an icon for the ~readme~ file.
  6) There are three files in the ~AmigaScope.lha~ archive:-
     A) ~AmigaScope~, the running software.
     B) ~AmigaScope.hlp~, the online help file. For this to work the file
        ~More~ MUST be installed on the computer and in the computers' PATH.
     C) ~Homeminder.dat~, a saved ~DAT~ file for you to view.
  7) Do NOT connect any hardware while the AMIGA is powered up.
  8) When the De-Archiving is complete double click on the ~AmigaScope~
     tool and the software will start running.
  9) The hardware does NOT need to be connected to see the software
     working.
 10) For FULL operation including the hardware refer to the ~Info~
     file in the ~Docs~ drawer.
 11) Read the ~Warning~ file.

